@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Sequence - adm/KnowledgeBase
hide footbox
skinparam sequence {
  actorBorderColor #0f172a
  actorBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantBorderColor #0f172a
  participantBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantFontColor #0f172a
  lifeLineBorderColor #94a3b8
  groupBorderColor #cbd5e1
  groupBackgroundColor #f8fafc
}
actor Kubernetes
participant Controller
participant BaseReconciler
participant "OSOKServiceManager" as ServiceManager
participant OCI
note over BaseReconciler,ServiceManager
shared resolution:
shared/diagrams/shared-resolution-sequence.svg
shared delete:
shared/diagrams/shared-delete-sequence.svg
end note
Kubernetes -> Controller: enqueue KnowledgeBase reconcile
Controller -> BaseReconciler: Reconcile(request)
BaseReconciler -> ServiceManager: reconcile desired KnowledgeBase
group Lookup and bind
alt tracked or explicit OCI identity already exists
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetKnowledgeBase
else tracked identity is missing
ServiceManager -> OCI: ListKnowledgeBases(filters:\ncompartmentId, displayName, id)
alt reusable OCI resource is not found
ServiceManager -> OCI: CreateKnowledgeBase
loop create pending CREATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetKnowledgeBase
end
else reusable OCI resource already exists
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetKnowledgeBase
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: persist resolved OCI identity in status
end
alt delete requested
group Delete
ServiceManager -> OCI: DeleteKnowledgeBase
ServiceManager -> OCI: confirm delete via GetKnowledgeBase\nor ListKnowledgeBases
loop delete pending DELETING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetKnowledgeBase or\nListKnowledgeBases
end
alt cleanup or finalizer release is blocked
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: retain delete state and retry
else delete completion observed
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: release finalizer after delete completion
end
end
else OCI state is retryable
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: requeue while OCI remains in\nCREATING, UPDATING, DELETING
else live state requires field-aware\ndrift evaluation
group Drift handling
note over ServiceManager,OCI
Supported update surface: definedTags,
displayName, freeformTags
Reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId
Lookup filters: compartmentId,
displayName, id
Lookup matching: exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING; duplicate matches
fail
end note
opt force-new or conflicting drift is detected
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: reject before OCI mutation
end
opt supported mutable drift is detected
ServiceManager -> OCI: Apply\nChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment,\nUpdateKnowledgeBase only for mutable\nfields definedTags, displayName,\nfreeformTags
loop update pending UPDATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetKnowledgeBase
end
end
ServiceManager -> OCI: run helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=DELETED
ServiceManager -> OCI: apply follow-up strategy\ncreate=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetKnowledgeBase;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetKnowledgeBase;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetKnowledgeBase/ListKnowledgeBases\nconfirm-delete
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: status=required,\nfinalizer=retain-until-confirmed-delete
end
BaseReconciler --> Controller: requeue on provisioning, updating,\nterminating
note right of ServiceManager
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-resolution-sequence.svg
shared delete diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-delete-sequence.svg
Start from the shared resolution sequence for
OCID binding, datasource pagination, and
create-or-update dispatch.
Layer the shared delete sequence when finalizer
retention, delete confirmation, work-request
polling, or Secret cleanup apply.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers follow the shared resolution and
delete sequences with imported waits and
controller-local policy.
service: adm
slug: knowledgebase
kind: KnowledgeBase
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase/ListKnowledgeBases
confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, displayName,
freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_adm_knowledge_bases filters
compartmentId, displayName, id; exact
compartmentId plus displayName unique match in
ACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING; duplicate matches
fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is only a
delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a
KnowledgeBase body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
KnowledgeBase OCID from work-request resources,
and then rereads GetKnowledgeBase before
settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.displayName
is present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING summaries.
Only displayName, freeformTags, and definedTags
reconcile in place; compartmentId remains
replacement-only and
ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment stays out of
scope for the published runtime.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the work
request is terminal and GetKnowledgeBase or
fallback ListKnowledgeBases confirms the
resource is gone.
end note
@enduml
